1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3487 By: McCane
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to labor; enacting nonsalaried public
school employees minimum wage; providing for
8 codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 197.18 of Title 40, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 All nonsalaried public school employee's wages shall be set at a
16 minimum of Fifteen Dollars ($15.00) per hour for hours worked in a
17 pay period. Any tips, gratuities, or other benefits may not apply
18 toward payment of the minimum hourly wage required in this section.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
